gomodel:SYNGO_4520  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: OGT is enriched in the postsynaptic density fraction of excitatory synapses as shown by cell fractionation and immunoblot analysis (Fig 1A,B) and by colocalization with the postsynaptic marker protein PSD-95 (Fig. 1C).\nFrom the resolution of light microscopy, one cannot discriminate between pre-and postsynaptic localization.\nAnother group (Akimoto et al. (2003) PMID: 12618343) has shown in the cerebellum that OGT is pre-and postsynaptic.\n\nAn immunoblot of the antibody is shown in Fig. 1A.\n\n12/02/2021 Dnyanada: Due to low resolution and lack of a presynaptic marker in the staining (to negate presynaptic localisation, Figure 1C), the term \"synapse\" was chosen. However, one must account for the enrichment of OGT in PSD fractionation as well as its crucial role in regulating postsynaptic AMPAR expression (SynGO ID: 4521) in favour of its postsynaptic localisation.. Experimental description: We developed a mouse model where OGT was deleted\ngenetically from mature brain neurons in vivo... (p. 1685) (PMID 26989246)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" ;
        dc:date           "2021-02-12" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4520" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

